#Text=Abigail Nims
#Text=Abigail Nims
#Text=is an Assistant Professor of Voice ( Mezzo-soprano ) at University of Colorado Boulder .
#Text=Early life and education
#Text=Nims holds degrees from Yale School of Music , Westminster Choir College , and Ohio Wesleyan University .
#Text=In 2005 , she was a Young Artist with Opera North and from 2007 to 2008 was an apprentice artist with the Santa Fe Opera .
#Text=In 2009 she was a Virginia Adams Fellow at the Carmel Bach Festival . [ 1 ]
#Text=Career

#Text=Nims had established herself as a soloist , and since 2011 had performed with the San Francisco Symphony , the Saint Paul Chamber Orchestra , the Indianapolis Symphony Orchestra , Detroit Symphony Orchestra , the São Paulo Symphony , National Symphony Orchestra , Orchestra Sinfonica di Milano Giuseppe Verdi , the Bach Festival Society of Winter Park ( FL ) , the Louisiana Philharmonic , and the Masterworks Choir and Orchestra at Carnegie Hall .

#Text=In Colorado , she had appeared as soloist with the Colorado Symphony , the Colorado Music Festival , the Colorado Springs Philharmonic , the Boulder Philharmonic , the Colorado MahlerFest , and is a regular participant with the Colorado Bach Ensemble .
#Text=Outside of Colorado , as an opera singer , she had performed with Opera Omaha and Florentine Opera . [ 2 ]

#Text=Nims had debuted as Veruca Salt in The Golden Ticket with Atlanta Opera during 2011/2012 season and then became a soloist in Messiah , a play in which she also performed during the 2012/2013 season with Masterwork Chorus under Andrew Megill ' s baton .
#Text=During same season , she was an Octavian in Der Rosenkavalier , at first with Quad City Symphony Orchestra and then with New York City Opera . [ 3 ]
#Text=In 2013 , she appeared in Les nuits d'été with Adrian Symphony and in Die Fledermaus as Prince Orlovsky with the Virginia Opera .
#Text=The same year , she reprised her role as Veruca Salt with Wexford Festival Opera and then appeared as Despina in Così fan tutte with Palm Beach Opera .

#Text=Following the success , she became a singer soloist , performing Mass in B Minor by Johann Sebastian Bach with San Francisco Symphony and eventually returned to the Saint Paul Chamber Orchestra to sing Haydn ' s Harmoniemesse . [ 3 ]
#Text=She also sang Mozart ' s Requiem with Quad City Symphony Orchestra and returning to the New York Philharmonic for its presentation of Janáček ' s The Cunning Little Vixen .

#Text=Her other notable repertoire include L'étoile with New York City Opera , Night of the Four Moons with Saint Paul Chamber Orchestra , Messiah with New Choral Society and roles of Zerlina in Don Giovanni with Opera New Jersey , Despina in Così fan tutte with Opera Grand Rapids , Cherubino in The Marriage of Figaro and Meg in Little Women , both with Opera Delaware , Hermia in A Midsummer Night 's Dream with The Princeton Festival ; Zefka in Janáček 's The Diary of One Who Disappeared with Gotham Chamber Opera and South American engagements such as singing Mahler ' s Symphony No. 2 at the Municipal Theatre of Santiago , Chile and both Mozart 's Vespare solennes de confessore and Michael Haydn 's Requiem with Masterwork Chorus . [ 3 ]
#Text=Awards

#Text=In 2016 , Nims and the Boston Baroque orchestra were nominated for Grammy Award in the Best Engineered Album and Best Opera Album in the Classical category for their recording of Claudio Monteverdi ' s opera Il ritorno d'Ulisse in patria . [ 4 ] [ 5 ]
